CS 2043.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: one programming course or equivalent programming experience. No previous knowledge of UNIX or expertise in any particular language is assumed.

CS 2110.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 1110 or CS 1112 or equivalent course on programming in a procedural language.

CS 2800.pre_coreq: Prerequisite or corequisite: one programming course or permission of instructor.

CS 3110.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2110 or equivalent programming experience. Prerequisite or corequisite: CS 2800. Should not be taken concurrently with CS 3410 or CS 3420.

CS 3152.pre_coreq: Prerequisite for programmers: CS 2110 or permission of the instructor. Prerequisite for designers: INFO 2450 and/or submission of art/design samples to instructor. Corequisite: ENGRC 3152.

CS 3410.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2110 or equivalent programming experience. Recommended prerequisite: CS 2024. Should not take CS 3110 concurrently.

CS 4120.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 3110 or permission of instructor, and CS 3420 or CS 3410. Corequisite: CS 4121.

CS 4152.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 3152, CS 3300 or CS 4620 or CS 4700 or CS 5414. Corequisite: ENGRC 4152.

CS 4160.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 3110 or permission of instructor. Students are expected to be proficient with programming (e.g. CS 2110), and proof (e.g. CS 2800 or a mathematics course numbered 3000 or above).

CS 4220.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: MATH 2210 or MATH 2940 or equivalent, knowledge of programming, CS 3220 or CS 4210/MATH 4250, or permission of the instructor.

CS 4700.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2110/ENGRD 2110 and CS 2800, or by permission of instructor.

CS 4701.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 4670, CS 4700, CS 4740, or CS 4780.

CS 4744.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: Elementary Python (CS 1133 suffices), LING 1101 or CS 2800 or PHIL 2310. Prerequisite for CS majors: Elementary Python and CS 2800.

CS 4758.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: MATLAB programming or permission of instructor.

CS 4780.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: probability theory (e.g. BTRY 3080, ECON 3130, MATH 4710, ENGRD 2700) and linear algebra (e.g. MATH 2940) and calculus (e.g. MATH 1920) and programming proficiency (e.g. CS 2110).

CS 4810.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2800 or permission of instructor.

CS 4850.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2800, MATH 1910, MATH 1920, MATH 2210 or MATH 2940.

CS 5120.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 3110 or permission of instructor, CS 3420 or CS 3410. Corequisite: CS 5121.

CS 5135.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: ORIE 5380/CS 5727 or some knowledge of linear programming.

CS 5150.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2110 or equivalent experience programming in Java or C++.

CS 5152.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 3152, CS 3300 or CS 4620 or CS 4700 or CS 5414. Corequisite: ENGRC 5152.

CS 5160.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 3110 or permission of instructor. Students are expected to be proficient with programming (e.g. CS 2110), and proof (e.g. CS 2800 or a mathematics course numbered 3000 or above).

CS 5223.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: MATH 2210 or MATH 2940 or equivalent, knowledge of programming, CS 3220 or CS 4210/MATH 4250 or permission of instructor.

CS 5412.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 4410 or permission of instructor.

CS 5678.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 5650, INFO 5340, or permission from the instructor.

CS 5780.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: probability theory (e.g. BTRY 3080, ECON 3130, MATH 4710, ENGRD 2700) and linear algebra (e.g. MATH 2940) and calculus (e.g. MATH 1920) and programming proficiency (e.g. CS 2110).

CS 5830.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2800 or equivalent, CS 4810 or mathematical maturity, or permission of instructor.

CS 5850.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2800, MATH 1910, MATH 1920, MATH 2210 or MATH 2940.

CS 6156.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: graduate standing in CS or CS majors with CS 3110 grade of B+ or better.

CS 6210.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: MATH 4310 or permission of instructor.

CS 6682.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: Python; MATH 2210, CS 2110, or CS 2112. Recommended prerequisite: MATH 2230, and/or CS 3110, and/or demonstrated knowledge of Javascript and basic Signal Processing.

CS 6740.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2110 or equivalent, a course in artificial intelligence or any relevant subfield (e.g., NLP, information retrieval, machine learning, Cornell CS courses numbered 47xx or 67xx). Proficiency with using machine learning tools (e.g., fluency at training an SVM, comfort with assessing a classifier's performance using cross-validation).

CS 6741.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2110 or equivalent programming experience, CS 4780/CS 5780 or CS 6780 or equivalent.

CS 6751.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: MATH 4310 or equivalent, MATH 4720, proficiency in C++ or Python. Recommended prerequisite for undergraduates: MAE 4180 or CS 4750/CS 5750/MAE 4760/ECE 4770. Familiarity with ROS is required.

CS 6784.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 4780 or CS 5780 or equivalents or permission of instructor.

CS 6785.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 2110, MATH 1920, MATH 2940, MATH 4710, or permission of instructor.

CS 7190.pre_coreq: Prerequisite: CS 6110 or permission of instructor.
